{
  "page": "Lord Paramount of the Trident",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ted_Nasmith_A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire_Riverrun.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/8d/Ted_Nasmith_A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire_Riverrun.jpg/300px-Ted_Nasmith_A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire_Riverrun.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"303\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/8d/Ted_Nasmith_A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire_Riverrun.jpg/450px-Ted_Nasmith_A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire_Riverrun.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/8d/Ted_Nasmith_A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire_Riverrun.jpg/600px-Ted_Nasmith_A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire_Riverrun.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ted_Nasmith_A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire_Riverrun.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a>, seat of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\">House Tully</a>, by Ted Nasmith ©</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Lord Paramount of the Trident</b> is a title granted by the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> to the liege lord of the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> within the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The title refers to the great river of the region, the <a href=\"/index.php/Trident\" title=\"Trident\">Trident</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Known_Lords_Paramount_of_the_Trident\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known Lords Paramount of the Trident</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Paramount_of_the_Trident&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Edmyn_Tully.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/07/Edmyn_Tully.png/300px-Edmyn_Tully.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"310\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/07/Edmyn_Tully.png/450px-Edmyn_Tully.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/07/Edmyn_Tully.png/600px-Edmyn_Tully.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Edmyn_Tully.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Edmyn_Tully\" title=\"Edmyn Tully\">Edmyn Tully</a>, from <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i> Blu-ray</div></div></div>\n<p>During <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\">House Tully</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a> were the first of the <a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">rivermen</a> support <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> against <a href=\"/index.php/Harren_Hoare\" title=\"Harren Hoare\">Harren Hoare</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Isles_and_the_Rivers\" title=\"King of the Isles and the Rivers\">King of the Isles and the Rivers</a>. After Harren's death in the <a href=\"/index.php/Burning_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Burning of Harrenhal\">burning of Harrenhal</a>, Aegon the Conqueror rewarded Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Edmyn_Tully\" title=\"Edmyn Tully\">Edmyn Tully</a> by granting him the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> and naming him Lord Paramount of the Trident.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Although the Tullys have long been powerful river lords,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_house_tully.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_house_tully.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> the domains of Riverrun yield smaller armies than those of the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Blackwood\" title=\"House Blackwood\">Blackwoods</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Bracken\" title=\"House Bracken\">Brackens</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Frey\" title=\"House Frey\">Freys</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Vance\" title=\"House Vance\">Vances</a>. The Tully lineage was less proud than that of the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Mallister\" title=\"House Mallister\">Mallisters</a>, and they were not as wealthy as as the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Mooton\" title=\"House Mooton\">Mootons</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Riverrun is a strong castle,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_riverrun.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_riverrun.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> but it is significantly smaller than ruined <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The Tullys have had difficulty at times in managing the quarrelsome river lords.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Paramount_of_the_Trident&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Paramount_of_the_Trident&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>With <a href=\"/index.php/Hoster_Tully\" title=\"Hoster Tully\">Hoster Tully</a>, Lord Paramount of the Trident, ailing at <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a>, his heir, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Edmure_Tully\" title=\"Edmure Tully\">Edmure Tully</a>, supports <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a>, the newly-crowned <a href=\"/index.php/King_in_the_North\" title=\"King in the North\">King in the North</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> and <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Trident\" title=\"King of the Trident\">King of the Trident</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the assassination of King <a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly Baratheon</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Storm%27s_End_(299)\" title=\"Siege of Storm&#39;s End (299)\">Storm's End</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>, the acting <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>, plot to form an alliance with <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tyrell\" title=\"House Tyrell\">House Tyrell</a> to win over any lords from the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a> or the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a> who did not immediately declare for King <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> after Renly's death. Petyr volunteers to travel to <a href=\"/index.php/Bitterbridge\" title=\"Bitterbridge\">Bitterbridge</a> to broker the deal,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> and then in <a href=\"/index.php/Highgarden\" title=\"Highgarden\">Highgarden</a> he is successful in forging a <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">Lannister</a>-Tyrell alliance through the engagement of King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey I Baratheon</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Margaery Tyrell\">Margaery Tyrell</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> the daughter of <a href=\"/index.php/Mace_Tyrell\" title=\"Mace Tyrell\">Mace Tyrell</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Paramount_of_the_Mander\" title=\"Lord Paramount of the Mander\">Lord Paramount of the Mander</a>.\n</p><p>Petyr returns to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> with Tyrell forces alongside those of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>. The allied armies are able to take Stannis's forces in the rear in the last hours of the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Battle of the Blackwater</a>, with Petyr providing the idea to dress Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Garlan_Tyrell\" title=\"Garlan Tyrell\">Garlan Tyrell</a> in the late King Renly's armor during the battle so as to frighten Stannis's <a href=\"/index.php/Men-at-arms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Men-at-arms\">men-at-arms</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the battle, Petyr is rewarded with the title Lord Paramount of the Trident and is made the new liege lord over the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> according to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>. Petyr is also made <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Lord of Harrenhal\">Lord of Harrenhal</a>, although the castle is still held by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Roose_Bolton\" title=\"Roose Bolton\">Roose Bolton</a> in Robb's name. Though Petyr has not set foot in <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>, the title gives him nominal control over the war-torn riverlands and elevates his rank considerably.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Paramount_of_the_Trident&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Hoster_Tully.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6c/Hoster_Tully.jpg/350px-Hoster_Tully.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"233\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6c/Hoster_Tully.jpg/525px-Hoster_Tully.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6c/Hoster_Tully.jpg/700px-Hoster_Tully.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Hoster_Tully.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Hoster_Tully\" title=\"Hoster Tully\">Hoster Tully</a>'s funeral in the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Fork\" title=\"Red Fork\">Red Fork</a>, by Jauma ©</div></div></div>\n<p>Hoster Tully passes away at Riverrun<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> and his successor, Lord Edmure Tully, is attainted by the Iron Throne<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos72.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos72.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> after being captured at the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Wedding\" title=\"Red Wedding\">Red Wedding</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In addition to becoming Lord Paramount of the Trident, Petyr Baelish becomes <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Protector_of_the_Vale\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lord Protector of the Vale\">Lord Protector of the Vale</a> after wedding Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Lysa_Arryn\" title=\"Lysa Arryn\">Lysa Arryn</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos68.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos68.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos80.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos80.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Paramount_of_the_Trident&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Having been named <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Riverrun\" title=\"Lord of Riverrun\">Lord of Riverrun</a> by the Iron Throne, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Emmon_Frey\" title=\"Emmon Frey\">Emmon Frey</a> assumes that he is now the liege of the <a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">rivermen</a>, including even his own father, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey\" title=\"Walder Frey\">Walder Frey</a>. At the <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Riverrun\" title=\"Siege of Riverrun\">siege of Riverrun</a>, however, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> explains to Emmon that Lord Petyr Baelish of Harrenhal is Lord Paramount.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_Lords_Paramount_of_the_Trident\">Known Lords Paramount of the Trident</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Paramount_of_the_Trident&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known Lords Paramount of the Trident\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Edmyn_Tully\" title=\"Edmyn Tully\">Edmyn Tully</a>, first Lord Paramount of the Trident.</li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Prentys_Tully\" title=\"Prentys Tully\">Prentys Tully</a>, ruled during the early reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>.</li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Grover_Tully\" title=\"Grover Tully\">Grover Tully</a>, a lord during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.</li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Elmo_Tully\" title=\"Elmo Tully\">Elmo Tully</a>, a lord during the Dance of the Dragons.</li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Kermit_Tully\" title=\"Kermit Tully\">Kermit Tully</a>, a lord during the Dance of the Dragons.</li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Medgar_Tully\" title=\"Medgar Tully\">Medgar Tully</a>, lord during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron II Targaryen</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Tully_(successor_of_Medgar)\" title=\"Lord Tully (successor of Medgar)\">Lord Tully</a>, Medgar's successor. A boy of eight in <a href=\"/index.php/211_AC\" title=\"211 AC\">211&#160;AC</a>. He ruled during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys I Targaryen\">Aerys I Targaryen</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Tully_(father_of_Hoster)\" title=\"Lord Tully (father of Hoster)\">Lord Tully</a>, the father of Lord Hoster. He ruled during the early reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys II Targaryen\">Aerys II Targaryen</a>.</li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Hoster_Tully\" title=\"Hoster Tully\">Hoster Tully</a>, stripped of the title by the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>.</li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a>, granted the title by the Iron Throne.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Paramount_of_the_Trident&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Pojypojy_Littlefinger.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/c6/Pojypojy_Littlefinger.jpg/300px-Pojypojy_Littlefinger.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"318\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/c/c6/Pojypojy_Littlefinger.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Pojypojy_Littlefinger.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a>, by Pojypojy ©</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>It is the wish of <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">the King's Grace</a> that his loyal councillor <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a> be rewarded for faithful service to crown and realm. Be it known that Lord Baelish is granted the castle of <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a> with all its attendant lands and incomes, there to make his seat and rule henceforth as Lord Paramount of the Trident. Petyr Baelish and his sons and grandsons shall hold and enjoy these honors until the end of time, and all <a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">the lords</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Trident\" title=\"Trident\">Trident</a> shall do him homage as their rightful liege.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Kevan_Lannister\" title=\"Kevan Lannister\">Kevan Lannister</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Hall_(Red_Keep)\" title=\"Great Hall (Red Keep)\">court</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Lord Paramount of the Trident, Sansa thought, and <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Lord of Harrenhal\">Lord of Harrenhal</a> as well. She did not understand why that should make him so happy; the honors were as empty as the title granted to <a href=\"/index.php/Hallyne\" title=\"Hallyne\">Hallyne the Pyromancer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Emmon</b>: Ser Jaime, <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">your lord father's</a> faith in me was well placed, you shall see. I mean to be firm but fair with my new vassals. <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Blackwood\" title=\"Tytos Blackwood\">Blackwood</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jonos_Bracken\" title=\"Jonos Bracken\">Bracken</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Jason_Mallister\" title=\"Jason Mallister\">Jason Mallister</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Vance\" title=\"House Vance\">Vance</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Clement_Piper\" title=\"Clement Piper\">Piper</a>, they shall learn that they have a just overlord in Emmon Frey. <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey\" title=\"Walder Frey\">My father</a> as well, yes. He is the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Crossing\" title=\"Lord of the Crossing\">Lord of the Crossing</a>, but I am the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Riverrun\" title=\"Lord of Riverrun\">Lord of Riverrun</a>. A son has a duty to obey his father, true, but a <a href=\"/index.php/Bannerman\" title=\"Bannerman\">bannerman</a> must obey his overlord.<br />\n</p><p><b>Jaime</b>: You are not his overlord, ser. Read your parchment. You were granted <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a> with its lands and incomes, no more. <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a> is the Lord Paramount of the Trident. Riverrun will be subject to the rule of <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>.<br />\n<b>Emmon</b>: Harrenhal is a ruin, haunted and accursed, and Baelish ... the man is a <a href=\"/index.php/Coin\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Coin\">coin</a> counter, no proper <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lord</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Dreadfort\" title=\"Dreadfort\">his birth</a> ...<br />\n</p>\n<b>Jaime</b>: If you are unhappy with the arrangements, go to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> and take it up with <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">my sweet sister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Emmon_Frey\" title=\"Emmon Frey\">Emmon Frey</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Paramount_of_the_Trident&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Aegon's Conquest.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_house_tully.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_house_tully.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Riverlands: House Tully.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7